Casablanca,ED3l5fWzFio,UgyHq9FusFw7hlxrMSF4AaABAg,,@crystalr7602,"At 66. I may be considered immature about my feelings about Casablanca, but I assure you, no one has more feeling of what happened back in those days as I. I am criticized by many for being into these old movies as if I lived back then and not into the ""newer"" movies. Movies these days don't have anywhere near the patriotism or sense of country as this movie when Paul Henried stood and rallied everyone to La Marsailles. I get so choked up from the patriotism it's like they say here - I cheer and cry for the lives of those back in those days. It's so amazing to me. Almost ashamed I get so emotional, but I do  and overcome with so much feeling you can't hold it in.",2025-04-23T01:45:28Z,2025-04-23T01:45:28Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-20T02:01:13.824956
