Rabat,nQSGx0PzMTs,UgwrI9zwhshGKMIY-Y94AaABAg,,@Boug0014,"It’s quite interesting with those street guides.  Some (I’m not saying all), don’t even know the history …. The Portuguese never occupied Rabat…. They occupied Maamoura in 1515 about 30km north of Rabat and Casablanca in also 1515.  But they never were in Rabat.  The Oudaya Kasbah was built by the Almohad Royal Family in 1150 as a fortification (Ribat) to fight the Berghwata Kingdom that extended from south of Rabat to about Essaouira.  The Kasbah was later used as a settlement for the Andalus Refugees after the fall of Granada and the expulsion of the Moriscos from Spain.",2026-03-20T05:22:59Z,2026-03-20T05:31:19Z,11,False,0.0,2026-05-20T02:01:32.302495
