Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAI9k8XtLhq0,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@tims7639,@FindingGinaMariethanks for the tip Judy. I’ll check out your other videos as well!,2025-05-15T22:37:18Z,2025-05-15T22:37:18Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.145296
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAJMGJclXMzv,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@cdeleo9336,@tims7639planning to go there will you share contacts of your guide,2025-06-14T15:49:27Z,2025-06-14T15:49:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.145303
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAJcg20wZ10Q,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,Hi @cdeleo9336: TimS used the same tour as we did. Here's the link: https://www.airbnb.com/experiences/604421 —Judy,2025-06-21T10:10:04Z,2025-06-21T10:10:04Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.145308
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugwm-74gikWd5EmR78l4AaABAg.AHLlqV6Pq1XAHNERjUGT4q,Ugwm-74gikWd5EmR78l4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Muhammed, We LOVE London. In fact our daughter was just there two days ago after visiting with us in Malta! May will be a nice time to visit Marrakech. The weather is hot but not unbearable, especially if you avoid the hottest parts of the day. And May is a month of celebrations. The Kelaa M'Gouna or Festival of the Rose runs from May 5-9 if you will be around to attend that. Have a terrific time! —Judy",2025-04-26T07:49:32Z,2025-04-26T07:49:32Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.263636
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxuUUq3xrtcndmn-Kx4AaABAg.AH93pO8FVUiAHDeSgIl9_t,UgxuUUq3xrtcndmn-Kx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Laura, The culture in Morocco is more modest, so if you want to respect the local culture, you won't wear clothes that are too revealing. I'm wearing tank tops, and my skirts are close to knee length, but you could cover your arms with an airy blouse and wear loose long pants or long skirts. I wasn't going to go out and buy these items since we're full time travelers, but I tried to be as modest as possible given my limited wardrobe. Morocco is reasonably understanding of tourists and don't necessarily expect them to follow all the Muslim customs. Personally, I wouldn't wear crop tops or show off my stomach or my full back or wear a bathing suit top (although we saw all of these by tourists). Does this help at all? —Judy",2025-04-22T14:33:11Z,2025-04-22T14:33:11Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.379037
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDUnluogM_,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Angela, There are no required vaccinations that the Moroccan government checks to see if you have had. However, with the monkeys in the Sahara, it wouldn't be the worst thing to have a rabies vaccination (we do not have that vaccination). We made sure that we had Hepatitis A, B, tetanus, MMR (measles, mumps, and rubella), typhoid, and cholera before we traveled to Egypt. If you have any specific concerns, it's not a bad idea to check with a travel doctor who can give you recommendations. But specific to Morocco? Nothing is required for entry. —Judy
🎥 Why we got vaccinated in Rome before heading to Egypt: https://youtu.be/ZJG4MI76u58
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-04-22T13:00:05Z,2025-04-22T13:00:05Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.493937
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDXfrhFZHe,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@Roathcourt,@ thank you so much Angela,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.493954
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg.AGx6eqm664_AGx71udc2kW,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We loved our time in Morocco! We especially enjoyed Fes, but we spent a month between Marrakech, the Sahara Desert, and Fes. We would definitely like to spend time exploring more of the country. —Judy",2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.619748
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg.AGsAZLPMU1UAGsBwyFqJ6j,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Syed, You will always be at the mercy of the border agent who you talk to. Offhand, I don't recall that they asked us anything. We may have had to show proof of onward travel afterwards and possibly the address of our riad where we were staying, but nothing else. These are common questions we get asked occasionally, but I think every agent does their own thing. It can also be dependent on your passport, and we are Americans. That's not to say in these unusual times that border agents will continue to be as kind to us. —Judy",2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.733417
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYDb2MBC3R,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Thelminetta, Neither of us recalls that we had to do that. Of course, you're always at the mercy of the specific passport security personnel you end up getting and possibly also your passport. You might enjoy our other episodes from our 40+ days in Morocco. —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-04-05T17:42:27Z,2025-04-05T17:42:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.869156
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYH2U3AXCU,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@thelminettas8694,"Thank you! I find your vlogs very informative. I avoid those that don’t teach - how to get to and from a destination, best location for accomodation, transportation, etc. My husband and I started traveling more and thought Marrakech and Fes are interesting cities to explore after Portugal and Spain in the fall. Thank you! I’m a subscriber now.",2025-04-05T18:12:33Z,2025-04-05T18:12:33Z,1,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.869173
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYhQuTvl7z,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We are so flattered. Thank you very much! You are right about Morocco being a perfect complement to those countries. We've been to Madrid and Barcelona, but people mentioned that Granada is a great place to visit before or after Morocco because there are certain similarities. After the Moors were expelled from Spain, many of them settled in Marrakech. Likewise certain North African dynasties once ruled parts of Spain, including Granada. We hope you have a great time! —Judy",2025-04-05T22:11:49Z,2025-04-05T22:11:49Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.869179
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugy_9L0ALq-j1Pw4eWZ4AaABAg.AGJSLva62MzAGJZ6ZzYi13,Ugy_9L0ALq-j1Pw4eWZ4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Thank you so much, Adil! It is super kind of you to say this. Thanks for watching, and we have a series from our 40+ days in Morocco if you're interested. I'll put a link to it below. —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-03-31T01:01:47Z,2025-03-31T01:01:47Z,1,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:50.996164
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzTQwvxzbqmQPHpizB4AaABAg.AGI_1P2lBjFAGIwOoh7MNZ,UgzTQwvxzbqmQPHpizB4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Wow, Bry, Thank you so much for your very kind words and for subscribing! Please tell your family and friends about us and share our videos. That is what YouTube likes to see and what helps others to find us. We are so grateful for the community we have here! And we loved our time in Morocco. We have a full series that we hope you enjoy. We visited the Sahara Desert and absolutely loved Fes! —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-03-30T19:14:45Z,2025-03-30T19:14:45Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:51.124661
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygYPhcCHOGoIbCWT14AaABAg.AEsOPMUEOXWAEubupeRRgI,UgygYPhcCHOGoIbCWT14AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,This may be the restaurant that you are referring to in Marrakech. It's where we had breakfast several of the days that we visited (but they also serve other meals as well): https://www.mandalasociety.co/marrakech. —Judy,2025-02-24T02:43:21Z,2025-02-24T02:43:21Z,1,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:51.295034
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyTkvvc5TMDaXXsxAR4AaABAg.AEro9JX76GPAErpYzBMHFL,UgyTkvvc5TMDaXXsxAR4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Donah, Hmmm. It's tricky. El Badi Palace was pretty cool. We enjoyed it a lot. We have heard from some of our viewers that they really liked the Berber Museum and Majorelle Garden, too. I think it mostly depends on what type of experience you are interested in. I've heard that the garden is one of the most photographed and well-known gardens in Morocco. If you're into fashion, perhaps knowing that the garden was once owned by fashion designer Yves Saint Laurent will tip the scale for you. We are more interested in the deeper history and architecture, which is why we prioritized El Badi Palace. Thanks so much for watching. We have a full series from Morocco that might be interesting to you. We really enjoyed our 40+ days there. We don't think you will go wrong with either site, but they are very different! —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-02-23T00:44:51Z,2025-02-23T00:44:51Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:51.441396
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxzUobM4Ce3CwnfQRB4AaABAg.AECEE66XrQyAEDOgDxr-mj,UgxzUobM4Ce3CwnfQRB4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Thank you so much for watching! We really think colorful is an accurate way to describe Marrakech! We have a full series from our 40+ days in Morocco if you're interested in watching! —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-02-06T22:32:27Z,2025-02-06T22:32:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:51.570916
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxgTojif_sIweHMebp4AaABAg.AE3KIek4Gb0AEAYfRHrC1D,UgxgTojif_sIweHMebp4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"It's hard for us to not be able to record in certain places, which is why we might opt to skip them. We'd rather put our budget on places we can more easily share with our viewers. Of course, there are times when it's worth it to us, but it's so much easier when they do allow photographs. We use Airbnb quite a bit, but especially in Fes, our riad served us a very hearty breakfast every day and we were really able to save a lot of money not having to chase down an extra meal every day. Our Marrakech location wasn't ideal and although breakfast was cheap, arranging it was a bit confusing, so we only ate in once. Thanks for sharing your experience! —Judy",2025-02-05T20:02:00Z,2025-02-05T20:02:00Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:01:51.708061
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyIVqczQ0iOrKhcO6l4AaABAg.ADlWeBG9LiQADlwbogMWm2,UgyIVqczQ0iOrKhcO6l4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We don't shop for souvenirs as full-time travelers with no home base, but we are glad to hear you enjoyed this trio of museums. We will have to come back and check them out. We were in the Atlas Mountains, but again we skipped some of the shopping. Thanks for the recommendation about Dar Zite. We have a full series from our 40+ days in Marrakech if you're interested in watching. It's linked below. —Judy
