Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,UgyrKDn4lbCOUnF9ctB4AaABAg.A5qgoxmCZtDA5skC_MZ9HY,UgyrKDn4lbCOUnF9ctB4AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,Thanks for watching. 😍,2024-07-14T16:34:48Z,2024-07-14T16:34:48Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:02:06.247980
Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,UgyZ46GNuHQFCfqIImR4AaABAg.A5cV_VTE1EpA5gLH7JawH5,UgyZ46GNuHQFCfqIImR4AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,Hello! Thank you for watching. The day trips are Essaouira and Ouzoud waterfalls. We booked the tours from our Riad. But we found out that you can also book in some shops in Marrakech. Just be careful of scams,2024-07-09T20:57:20Z,2024-07-09T20:57:20Z,0,True,,2026-05-20T02:02:06.356975
Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,UgxN5S78vbnksl1BgXB4AaABAg.A5anRUCGmJtA5cRYqUID4v,UgxN5S78vbnksl1BgXB4AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,"Hello there Tom! There are indeed scams but for us they are very obvious. Also it was a great help that we watched a lot of videos before going there so we already knew what to avoid. For example, a random man who says that the way is closed then he will guide us to the correct way. Then he will ask money when you will arrive to the place. Do not believe them and just say no thank you. A lot of the merchants will be very friendly to you too and ask where are you from to start a conversation. We just answered them politely but we kept walking to where we were headed. If you know are lost for example in the souks because it’s like a labyrinth, just ask a merchant and probably avoid asking a random guy in the street. We were fine. We avoided “rough” areas. We used common sense. They are not going to hurt you. Some of them are just trying to earn money. Just ignore or say thank you. We felt safe in general. A lot of them are very friendly too. We met a family who just wanted to speak and practice their English. We are still in contact with them and invited us to visit their town.",2024-07-08T08:35:13Z,2024-07-08T08:35:13Z,4,True,,2026-05-20T02:02:06.496134
Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,UgxN5S78vbnksl1BgXB4AaABAg.A5anRUCGmJtA5cS39vo_3G,UgxN5S78vbnksl1BgXB4AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,"About the second question, Sardinia and Morocco are totally different. It depends on what you want to experience.

Sardinia is for beautiful Mediterranean coasts, coastal towns, chill life, amazing well kept nature, friendly locals, good food.

Morocco if you want to experience North African culture, more lively chaotic but unique culture, good food, mix of African and European architecture. And by the way, Moroccan architecture is impeccable and incomparable. They have one of the best designs I’ve ever seen. As a matter of fact, I want a touch of Moroccan design in my future house. Haha!! 

So if you decide which ones you want to experience, choose one. If you have more questions, feel free to ask us. We have Sardinia videos too.",2024-07-08T08:39:38Z,2024-07-08T08:39:38Z,3,True,,2026-05-20T02:02:06.496151
Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,UgxN5S78vbnksl1BgXB4AaABAg.A5anRUCGmJtA5cSCD2BxE8,UgxN5S78vbnksl1BgXB4AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,"Also, be careful of other videos describing the scams in Morocco. We found them too exaggerated. We’re not saying that scamming doesn’t exist but sometimes they were too much. And I think it is becoming more and more famous through social media so they are more careful now too.",2024-07-08T08:40:52Z,2024-07-08T08:40:52Z,2,True,,2026-05-20T02:02:06.496156
