Tangier,lJn9ziR6Zig,UgwPI0edW2mQSX1t8tZ4AaABAg,,@randombystander5324,"Tangier is a pretty interesting place to visit. The place has been settled at least since the pheonicians. It has a pretty large, well maintained, labyrinthine Medina (an arab old town) and around that are the less ancient city parts where you can find french style cafés that seems to have been frozen in the sixties (wonder why). They also have an abandoned bull fighting arena (you can't visit).
A downside is the modern moroccan city around it. It is completly car centric in the worst way possible. And unlike basically anywhere else in the world, if you are a non-muslim, you are not allowed to enter any mosques.
Another good quirk the city has is the ferry to Traifa in Spain. Absolutely worth a daytrip (you could also do it the other way around). If you get up early and are willing to pay for the taxi-ride, you can also continue to Gibraltar from there.

A recommendation for everyone who wants to try vacationing  outside the super secure countries  of the Global North without going too far off the beaten track yet.",2026-01-26T13:56:13Z,2026-01-26T13:56:13Z,1,False,2.0,2026-05-20T02:02:30.970773
