Tangier,lJn9ziR6Zig,Ugy9NtI4K_-petMu6EB4AaABAg,,@oligarchy73,"Funnily enough, after suffering the same fate as Hong Kong when its special privileges were “removed”, the Moroccan government seems to be backtracking and once again imitating Chinese policy, especially Deng Xiaoping’s idea of Special Economic Zones such as those around the Tanger Med port, to foster foreign investment and economic growth, much like China did.
Really cool video! As a Spanish-Moroccan, I love Tangiers, and I’m glad you made a video about the city because it’s truly fascinating.
And if anyone wants to delve deeper into the city’s history, I recommend reading the autobiographical trilogy of Mohammed Choukri, especially the first book, For Bread Alone. It really shows how international, bohemian, and open the city was back then compared to nowadays. It was pretty spot on a tax heaven, the economy was thriving, and there were plenty of, let’s say, decadent activities, so it was a sort of Monaco of Africa.",2026-01-23T22:07:24Z,2026-01-23T22:07:24Z,10,False,3.0,2026-05-20T02:02:30.971038
