Tangier,lJn9ziR6Zig,UgxTKECBKDWrXCiQp8R4AaABAg,,@simongiesen2664,"Hey tigerstar, have you ever heard of neutral moresnet? It came to be due to similar circumstances - although it was formed in the post napoleonic instead of the colonial era. It was a narrow strip of land containing Europe's most productive zinc mine which was semi independent. It functioned similarly to the Tangiers zone although on paper it was shared between the Netherlands (later Belgium) and Prussia. Fun fact, after the mine closed they tried for full independence by becoming the world's first Esperanto state, Amikejo. Well worth your while to make a video on I say!",2026-01-23T22:03:52Z,2026-01-23T22:03:52Z,15,False,0.0,2026-05-20T02:02:30.971049
