Tourism,Rl_YSqygFEM,UgwroGXo_Bti07-AVqZ4AaABAg.AIn4B17nWIrAOO7q7bqZO4,UgwroGXo_Bti07-AVqZ4AaABAg,@jurgenolivieiraJPCO,"​@CaptnProton68 It's not just about the trash, it's about the graffiti, carvings in the bamboo. Rudeness, loudness, trespassing, ignoring signes, etc., etc. Those things are common in the West bit very inpolite, uncommon, rare if not forbidden. Talking loud in public is frowned upon, and seen as rude and inconsidered, let alone everything else. When in Rome do as the Romans do. Some if these are the same people that scream ""speak American"" to tourists in their own country.",2025-10-17T15:50:50Z,2025-10-17T15:50:50Z,1,True,,2026-05-20T02:02:43.588946
