Warren buffett said, no one wants to do business with liers, so being honest and good human being is more profitable in long run.
And essesntial for stable business and stability of the society.
Japan is same thing, 18th century japanese philosopher  named Baigan Ishida wrote a book about business ethics and it was one of the best seller of the time in japan, he gave story of rich and successful merchant had a 2 son, he needed to decide which one will inherit his shop and money.
His eldest bright and talented kid, one day he scammed his customer, his servants finds out and fixed it, then master of the house finds out, the servant begged the master to forgive his son, since customer never found out the defect in the product and service and they fixed it before anyone can find out.
And the eldest son is very smart and talented kid, he should forgive him.
The father merchant, the master of the house said, dishonest man is not suited to be merchant, send him to be peasant.
And master of the house appointed his 2nd son, who is not as smart as his eldest son but had honest heart to be his successor.

This was taught as basis of japanese businessman.
Even to this day, japanese businessman values trust and honesty more than anything.
American business man are same thing, honesty, integrity is the most important mindset and virtue to be businessman.

Phillipino only learned money worshipping from americans, but never learned the importance of how honesty and trustworthyness is vital for the business and economy from Americans.

Also both japanese and americans are frugal, regular pinoys likes to spend money, but not think about saving money.

Phillipines needs to glorify, individualism, independency, frugality, honesty and integrity(specially in business).
They could become rich.

